The paper discusses security and privacy issues related to the use of Bitcoin over Tor, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential for creating a virtual Bitcoin reality, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of stealthy man-in-the-middle attacks, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
